rewards.textDesc:
A page from a poetry anthology in Taran.
The poem will be all too familiar to most Victorians, as it is often required reading at secondary school.

A written invitation from Count Philip.
Possibly due to changes in the date and venue, this invitation is void by now.

A transport permit acquired by Heidi through due means.
It comes with a full page of restrictive terms.

A photo of a soldier, 'Bill.'
Seeing his picture now prompts the Self-Salvation Corps to look away with mixed feelings.

A black feather.
The black fowlbeasts have flown for the storm.

unlockData.initialDes: A book of personal notes discovered among our materials. Unclear which Londinier lost it, and uncertain if they are still alive. Tells of much that is happening in the city at the moment. Can be perused in the intervals between battle.
unlockData.finalDes: A notebook Heidi sought to pass to Rhodes Island mere days before being arrested, now returned to its rightful owner. Much that has happened in this city is recorded in a terse, obfuscated style. Heidi is more than glad to let you borrow it to peruse as often as you like.
unlockData.remindDes: While perusing the notes, you found an ID card, and on it a familiar name. Based on the handwriting both preceding and following, you can be sure she was the owner of the notebook.

rewards.textDesc:
A lookout tower standing tall in front of the Palace.
Being from several centuries ago, the tower has long since crumbled, leaving only a sketch to provide posterity a notion of what it originally looked like.

The identifying badge of the Captain of the Watch, who leads the Knights of the Tower.
An honor, and doubly so a responsibility.

The highest military award issued by Victoria.
Only found in the possession of truly heroic Victorian soldiers. You'll find more than one hanging in the White Wolf family hall, to boot.

A newspaper clipping filled with jubilation.
That day, all of Victoria's papers sang praises of Frederick III and his feat of conquering Gaul.

A clipping of the Palace amidst firelight.
No one knows where Victoria is headed.

unlockData.initialDes:
The Book of the Tower Knights, chronicling centuries of life for the Knights of the Tower.
Lent to you by Dagda for your perusal, serving as a window into Victoria's history.

rewards.textDesc: Ol' Baldy Per's business in the district was doing so well it may as well have been on fire, but his appearance was the laughingstock of his customers. He even scared away more than a few noblewomen. In a stroke of ingenuity, he got himself a new gold tooth to bless his bakery with good fortune. He never expected his shop to really take off like that.

At the closing ceremony of the third Columbian Heraldry Conference, a young, no-name scholar had the opportunity to give a speech in the place of his instructor, who received an award. The instructor then gave the medal to the young scholar, encouraging him to become a rising star in the field of Victorian heraldry. For a time, the bond between teacher and pupil became the talk of the town.

In their fight against the Sarkaz, the leaders of the Norport Borough gangs reached a strange understanding on how to protect their neighborhood. They were planning to spearhead the resistance at the supply lines. Regardless of the outcome of their partnership, this was great news for the youngsters in love with people in their rival gangs.

Watching explicit films is always a good way to alleviate stress during wartime. McClaren understood this, which is why he made good money showing these flicks, unauthorized for public viewing. Come to think of it, though, who would come enforce it anyway, given everything that was going on?

Baird still remembered that when she showed off her new butterfly knife to the Glasgow members, Indra suggested making it gang property and stamped their seal onto its hilt. Although the two of them got into a fight over this, according to Vina, Baird seemed somewhat open to the idea.

unlockData.initialDes: A box of personal effects treasured by a cleaner wandering Norport Borough. The box contains many ownerless objects collected from the tattered district. Perhaps it can help you uncover the dark side of this city, buried beneath the dust of the battlefield.

rewards.textDesc:
I remember. She was adorable. ‚ÄîAnne
Dad, I like my present! I'm just upset because Mum was too late to take pictures!
Business held me up. I'll be careful next time. ‚ÄîMum

(Cipher has been decrypted)
Mum, Dad taught me how to write in code‚ÄîWhat do you think? He praised my talent for understanding 'what is worthwhile information' too!
By the way, I've found out that the railways and trains here have all adopted our Victorian standards. Dad says it's because the Duke of Caster has been backing the transformation of Kjerag, but we don't need to worry about that.
It is just as I promised when I knelt before you on that fateful night. 'Til death do us part, I shall be your vassal, my Duke.' ‚ÄîKent Windermere

(Cipher has been decrypted)
I found this card among Dad's belongings. He left a message on it too. It may be of no matter to you at this point, though.
The Dukes of Stafford and Cavendish certainly aren't. I'll be keeping a closer eye on the Duke of Caster.
I've looked into the Duke of Ashworth; his 'benefactor' hasn't made clear his position on Victoria's future as of yet. Very odd. ‚ÄîKent

That 'difficult decision' was never for the sake of any actual person. Maybe the ducal system you so upheld as the beating heart of Victoria has long ceased to be necessary to Her, Dad.
But I'll always be proud of you. I wish I could tell you that face to face, more than anything.
‚ÄîDelphine

unlockData.initialDes: Postcards from all over Terra, preserved for many years. What Delphine's been collecting since childhood. A record of the three-person household's happy days of yore, now given to you by Delphine herself to be sealed away. 'Bygones are bygones. I don't mind you taking a peek, of course.'
